<br>
A caveat, however -- running a PHP front-end/MySQL back-end forum to sustain hundreds of simultaneous users will require a dedicated server, and these, themselves, are not cheap at all (they usually range between $100 to $400 a month, depending upon your level of managed support systems). In the long run, though, you ultimately get much better software performance and control. On my web sites, I use vBulletin, but phpBB (which is free) is also extremely stable.<br>
